<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<section xml:lang="en" xml:id="element-quote" class="element"
	xmlns="http://purl.oclc.org/NET/dml/1.0/"
	xmlns:cdml="http://purl.oclc.org/NET/cdml/1.0/"
	xmlns:dct="http://purl.org/dc/terms/">

	<title>The <cdml:node role="element">quote</cdml:node> element</title>
	<metadata>
		<list>
			<item property="dct:description">A quotation.</item>
		</list>
	</metadata>
	<p>The <cdml:node role="element">quote</cdml:node> element represents a generic quotation container.</p>
	<list>
		<item>
			<title>Flow</title>
			<p>When its parent is an inline element or a block element that only allows inline elements its flow is <span href="#inline-flow">inline</span>, otherwise its flow is <span href="#block-flow">block</span>.</p>
		</item>
		<item>
			<title>Children</title>
			<cdml:code language="xpath">
( $block[not( quote | citation )]+ citation | ( $inline | text() )+ )
			</cdml:code>
		</item>
		<item>
			<title>Attributes</title>
			<cdml:code language="xpath">
( $core.attrs* | $meta.attrs* | @citation? )
			</cdml:code>
		</item>
		<item>
			<title>Parents</title>
			<cdml:code language="xpath">
( dml | $block[not( quote | citation )] | $inline[not( quote )] )
			</cdml:code>
		</item>
	</list>

	<p>The <cdml:node role="attribute">citation</cdml:node> attribute <em>must</em> be used to provide the URI (<cdml:datatype>xs:anyURI</cdml:datatype>) of the resource cited when the flow of <cdml:node role="element">quote</cdml:node> element is <em>inline</em>, otherwise <em>must not</em> be used.</p>


	<example xml:id="ex-block-quote" status="draft">
		<title>Usage of block flow <cdml:node role="element">quote</cdml:node> element.</title>
		<cdml:code language="xml">
&lt;section&gt;
  ( … )
  &lt;quote&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Lorem ipsum&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;citation&gt;??? &lt;span href="http://some.resource"&gt;???&lt;/span&gt; ??? &lt;/citation&gt;
  &lt;/quote&gt;
  ( … )
&lt;/section&gt;
		</cdml:code>
	</example>

	<example xml:id="ex-inline-quote" status="draft">
		<title>Usage of inline flow <cdml:node role="element">quote</cdml:node> element.</title>
		<cdml:code language="xml">
&lt;p&gt;
  ??? &lt;quote citation="http://some.resource"&gt;cite&lt;/quote&gt; ???
&lt;/p&gt;
		</cdml:code>
	</example>


</section>